THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

keymesh has ZERO required runtime dependencies. The provider adapters use
OPTIONAL peer dependencies, resolved only when the matching adapter is
imported. Each is distributed under its own license:

  - openai (OpenAI)            — Apache-2.0
  - @anthropic-ai/sdk (Anthropic) — MIT
  - @google/genai (Google)     — Apache-2.0

The core package and the generic HTTP adapter use only the runtime's built-in
fetch and Node standard library; they pull in none of the above.

Development-only tooling (NOT shipped in the published package):

  - tsup            — MIT
  - vitest          — MIT
  - typescript      — Apache-2.0
  - @biomejs/biome  — MIT OR Apache-2.0
  - publint         — MIT
